Selenium : 

1)IDE ->Record and play tool
2)RC ->selenium1 deprecated
3) WebDriver -> Selenium WD  2->3-> 4.x
4) Selenium Grid : os/browsers ->Parallel -remote/Server/Cloud

Pros:
Selenium is open source- customize ->WDio, appium,contribute
-free license tool
-cross browser support -- chrome, firefox,edge, safari
- cross platform --windows, Mac, linux 
but it doesnt support unix 
--multiple language binding support- Java,python,Js, Ruby,php,c#
--W3c webdriver protocol
World wide web consortium -Selenium is w3c certified.
-->browsers(W3c) <--> Automation tool (W3c)
-- Can be integrated with any third party tools like jenkins, TestNg,Maven, Log4J.
-- screenshot, scrolling
--pop ups,tab, shadow dom,frames, tab

Cons:
1)It only automates browsers/web application.
2)can not automate mobile native apps.
3) Can not perform APi automation.
4) -just a lib/tool which automates browsers using some actions like click, sendKeys,gettext,open browser.
5) integrate it with unit testing frameworks : testng/junit, Pytest,Nunit,phpunit.
6) It cannot generate any test result/report/htmlreport.
7)It cannot do performance testing/security Testing
8) captcha,bar code,QR code.
9)--mail APIS,


